Training Our Models

Preparing the Data

def splitter(df):
    x = df.iloc[:,:-1]
    y = df.iloc[:,-1:]
    xtrain, x_rem, ytrain, y_rem = train_test_split(x,y, test_size=0.2, train_size=0.8, random_state=3, shuffle=True, stratify=y)
    xtest, xvalid, ytest, yvalid = train_test_split (x_rem, y_rem, test_size = 0.5, random_state=3, shuffle=True, stratify= y_rem)
    xtrain = np.array(xtrain)
    ytrain = np.array(ytrain.values.ravel())
    xtest = np.array(xtest)
    ytest = np.array(ytest.values.ravel())
    xvalid = np.array(xvalid)
    yvalid = np.array(yvalid.values.ravel())
    return xtrain, ytrain, xtest, ytest, xvalid, yvalid

def prep_data(discrete_features = ['vis_wuhan', 'from_wuhan', 'gender', *symptoms, 'country', 'location'], cont_features = ['age', 'diff_sym_hos'], hot_encode_disc = True, hot_encode_cont = False, normalize_cont = True):
    df_copy = df[[*(discrete_features+cont_features+['result'])]].copy()    
    if normalize_cont:
        df_copy[[*cont_features]] = (df_copy[[*cont_features]]-df_copy[[*cont_features]].min())/(df_copy[[*cont_features]].max()-df_copy[[*cont_features]].min())
    if hot_encode_cont:
        df_copy['age'] = pd.cut(df_copy.age, bins=[0,0.3, 0.5, 0.7, 1], labels=['Baby', 'child', 'Adult', 'Elderly'])
        df_copy['diff_sym_hos'] = pd.cut(df_copy.diff_sym_hos, bins=[0, 0.4, 0.7, 1], labels=['near', 'medium', 'far'])
        df_copy = pd.concat([df_copy, pd.get_dummies(df_copy['age'], prefix = 'age')], axis=1)
        df_copy = pd.concat([df_copy, pd.get_dummies(df_copy['diff_sym_hos'], prefix = 'diff_sym_hos')], axis=1)
        df_copy = df_copy.drop('age', axis = 1)
        df_copy = df_copy.drop('diff_sym_hos', axis = 1)

    if hot_encode_disc:
        for i in discrete_features:
            if i == 'vis_wuhan' or i == 'from_wuhan':
                continue
            df_copy = pd.concat([df_copy, pd.get_dummies(df_copy[i], prefix = i)], axis=1)
            df_copy = df_copy.drop([i], axis = 1)
    df_copy = df_copy.drop('result', axis = 1) #dropping unnecessary columns
    df_copy = pd.concat([df_copy, df['result']], axis=1) #shifting the result column to the end
    xtrain, ytrain, xtest, ytest, xvalid, yvalid = splitter(df_copy)
    return df_copy, xtrain, ytrain, xtest, ytest, xvalid, yvalid
df_ready, x_train, y_train, x_test, y_test, x_valid, y_valid = prep_data()

#Accuracy function
def scoring(preds, ytest):
    return 1 - np.mean(np.abs(ytest-preds))

Using our Implemented Function

#calculating Euclidean distances to build a matrix of the indices of the corresponding nearest k points 
def dist(a, b, k): 
    d = (np.argsort((np.sum((a[:,np.newaxis]-b)**2 ,axis=2))**(1/2), axis=1))[:,:k]
    return d

#classifying the points according to their nearest neighbors
def classify(d,ytrain, k):
    preds = []
    for i in range(len(d)):
        summ = 0
        for m in d[i]:
            summ += ytrain[m]
        if (summ/k) > 0.5:
            preds.append(1)
        else:
            preds.append(0)
    return preds
def knn(xtrain, ytrain, xtest, kn):
    d = dist(xtest, xtrain, kn)
    preds = classify(d, ytrain, kn)
    return preds

Logistic Regression

Using our Implemented Function

# sigmoid function
def sigmoid(z):
    return 1/(1 + np.exp(-z))

# Output prediction function
def logistic_predict(features, weights):
    features = np.float_(features)
    weights = np.float_(weights)
    return sigmoid((np.matmul(weights, features.T))) 

# Cross-Entropy function
def cross_entropy(ytest, preds):
    ytest = np.float_(ytest)
    preds = np.float_(preds)
    return - ytest * np.log(preds) - (1 - ytest) * np.log(1 - preds)

# Gradient descent function
def update_weights(xtrain, ytrain, weights, learnrate): 
    output = logistic_predict(xtrain, weights)
    diff = np.array(ytrain - output)
    weights  = weights + np.sum(learnrate *  diff[:, np.newaxis] * xtrain, axis = 0)
    return weights

def classify_log(log_preds):
    return (log_preds >= 0.5).astype(int)
np.random.seed(3)
def logistic_regress(xtrain, ytrain, xvalid, yvalid, xtest, ytest, epochs = 1000, learnrate = 0.01):
    xtrain = np.insert(xtrain, 0, values=1, axis=1)
    xvalid = np.insert(xvalid, 0, values=1, axis=1)
    weights = np.random.uniform(size = xtrain.shape[1])
    max_acc = 0
    opt_weights = weights
    print("TRAINING & VALIDATING... \n")
    for i in range(epochs):
        for k in range(10):
            weights = update_weights(xtrain, ytrain, weights, learnrate)
        preds = logistic_predict(xvalid, weights)
        validation_classified_preds = classify_log(logistic_predict(xvalid, weights))
        acc = scoring(validation_classified_preds, yvalid)
        if max_acc < acc:
            max_acc = acc
            opt_weights = weights
        print("Epoch ", i*10)
        print("Loss = ", np.mean(cross_entropy(yvalid, preds)))
        print("Accuracy = ", acc)
        print("\n\n")
    print("\n\n")
    print("TESTING...")
    xtest = np.insert(xtest, 0, values=1, axis=1)
    preds_t = logistic_predict(xtest, opt_weights)
    print("Loss = ", np.mean(cross_entropy(ytest, preds_t)))
    test_classified_preds = classify_log(logistic_predict(xtest, opt_weights))
    acc = scoring(test_classified_preds, ytest)
    print("Accuracy = ", acc)
    plt.title('Plotting The Sigmoid Function Against the Data')
    yt = sigmoid(np.matmul(opt_weights, xtrain.T))
    plt.plot(xtrain, yt, 'r.')
    plt.plot(xtrain, ytrain, 'b.')
    return test_classified_preds
logistic_predictions = logistic_regress(x_train, y_train, x_valid,y_valid, x_test, y_test)

    return (1 / (math.sqrt(2 * math.pi) * var)) * expo

Discrete Naive Bayes Implementation

def naive_bayes(xtrain, ytrain, xtest):
    prior0 = np.sum(ytrain == 0)/len(ytrain)
    prior1 = np.sum(ytrain == 1)/len(ytrain)
    #xtrain_inv = (np.logical_not(xtrain.copy())).astype(int)
    #calculating all likelihoods
    likelihoods1 = np.concatenate((np.sum(xtrain[np.where(ytrain==1)], axis = 0)/np.sum(ytrain == 1),
                            1-(np.sum(xtrain[np.where(ytrain==1)], axis = 0)/np.sum(ytrain == 1))))
    likelihoods0 = np.concatenate((np.sum(xtrain[np.where(ytrain==0)], axis = 0)/np.sum(ytrain == 0), 
                            1-(np.sum(xtrain[np.where(ytrain==0)], axis = 0)/np.sum(ytrain == 0))))
    #broadcasting the xtest data 
    xtest = np.column_stack((xtest, (np.logical_not(xtest)).astype(int)))
    #fitering the irrelevant likelihoods
    likelihoods0_m = xtest * likelihoods0
    likelihoods1_m = xtest * likelihoods1
    #Swapping zeroes for ones, so that row multiplication of likelihoods isn't zeroed out
    likelihoods0_m[likelihoods0_m==0] = 1
    likelihoods1_m[likelihoods1_m==0] = 1
    #row multiplication of likelihoods
    likelihoods1_m = np.prod(likelihoods1_m, axis=1)
    likelihoods0_m = np.prod(likelihoods0_m, axis = 1)
    #calculating the relative predictions
    relative_pred = (likelihoods1_m * prior1)/(likelihoods0_m * prior0)
    return (relative_pred >= 1).astype(int)

Gaussian Naive Bayes Implementation

def gaussian_m(sigma, mu, x, d):
    sigma_inv = np.linalg.inv(sigma * np.identity(d))
    expo = np.exp(-1/2*(np.sum(((x-mu) @ sigma_inv) * (x-mu), axis=1)))
    return (1/(pow(2*np.pi, d/2)*pow(np.linalg.det(sigma * np.identity(d)), 1/2)))*expo
def gauss_nb_m(xtrain, ytrain, xtest):
    mu_1 = (1/len(xtrain))*np.sum(xtrain[np.where(ytrain==1)], axis=0)
    sigma_1 = (1/len(xtrain)) * np.sum((xtrain[np.where(ytrain==1)]-mu_1)**2, axis = 0)
    mu_0 = (1/len(xtrain))*np.sum(xtrain[np.where(ytrain == 0)], axis=0)
    sigma_0 = (1/len(xtrain)) * np.sum((xtrain[np.where(ytrain == 0)]-mu_0)**2, axis = 0)
    preds =gaussian_m(sigma_1, mu_1, xtest, xtrain.shape[1])/gaussian_m(sigma_0, mu_0, xtest, xtrain.shape[1])
    return (np.array(preds) >= 1).astype(int)

def naive_bayes_final(xtrain_c, xtrain_d, ytrain, xtest_c, xtest_d):
    prior0 = np.sum(ytrain == 0)/len(ytrain)
    prior1 = np.sum(ytrain == 1)/len(ytrain)
    #xtrain_inv = (np.logical_not(xtrain.copy())).astype(int)
    #calculating all likelihoods
    likelihoods1 = np.concatenate((np.sum(xtrain_d[np.where(ytrain==1)], axis = 0)/np.sum(ytrain == 1),
                            1-(np.sum(xtrain_d[np.where(ytrain==1)], axis = 0)/np.sum(ytrain == 1))))
    likelihoods0 = np.concatenate((np.sum(xtrain_d[np.where(ytrain==0)], axis = 0)/np.sum(ytrain == 0), 
                            1-(np.sum(xtrain_d[np.where(ytrain==0)], axis = 0)/np.sum(ytrain == 0))))
    #broadcasting the xtest data 
    xtest_d = np.column_stack((xtest_d, (np.logical_not(xtest_d)).astype(int)))
    #fitering the irrelevant likelihoods
    likelihoods0_m = xtest_d * likelihoods0
    likelihoods1_m = xtest_d * likelihoods1
    #Swapping zeroes for ones, so that row multiplication of likelihoods isn't zeroed out
    likelihoods0_m[likelihoods0_m==0] = 1
    likelihoods1_m[likelihoods1_m==0] = 1
    #row multiplication of likelihoods
    likelihoods1_m = np.prod(likelihoods1_m, axis=1)
    likelihoods0_m = np.prod(likelihoods0_m, axis = 1)
    #calculating the relative predictions    
    mu_1 = (1/len(xtrain_c))*np.sum(xtrain_c[np.where(ytrain==1)], axis=0)
    sigma_1 = (1/len(xtrain_c)) * np.sum((xtrain_c[np.where(ytrain==1)]-mu_1)**2, axis = 0)
    mu_0 = (1/len(xtrain_c))*np.sum(xtrain_c[np.where(ytrain == 0)], axis=0)
    sigma_0 = (1/len(xtrain_c)) * np.sum((xtrain_c[np.where(ytrain == 0)]-mu_0)**2, axis = 0)
    relative_pred = (likelihoods1_m * gaussian_m(sigma_1, mu_1, xtest_c, xtrain_c.shape[1])* prior1)/(likelihoods0_m * gaussian_m(sigma_0, mu_0, xtest_c, xtrain_c.shape[1]) * prior0)
    return (relative_pred >= 1).astype(int)

##gini calculation
def gini_calc(y):
    y_unique, counts = np.unique(y, return_counts=True)
    p = counts/len(y)
    gini = 1-np.sum(p**2)
    return gini
##entropy calculation
def entropy_calc(y):
    y_unique, counts = np.unique(y, return_counts=True)
    p = counts/len(y)
    entropy = np.sum(-p*np.log2(p))
    return entropy
##impurity calculation with criterion parameter
def impurity(feature, criterion):
    imp = 0
    if criterion == 'gini':
        imp = gini_calc(feature)
    elif criterion == 'entropy':
        imp = entropy_calc(feature)
    else:
        print("invalid criterion")

    return imp
class Node:
    def __init__(self, feature, value, left_child, right_child, impurity, data):
        self.feature = feature
        self.value = value
        self.left_child = left_child
        self.right_child = right_child
        self.impurity = impurity
        self.data = data
def best_ig(node, criterion):
    max_ig = 0
    best_feature= 0
    best_value = 0
    best_ln = np.array([])
    best_rn = np.array([])
    for i in range(0,len(node.data[0,:])-1):
        for k in np.unique(node.data[:,i]):
            ln = node.data[node.data[:,i] == k]
            rn = node.data[node.data[:,i] != k]
            ig = node.impurity - ((len(ln)/len(node.data)) * impurity(ln[:, -1],criterion) 
            + (len(rn)/len(node.data)) * impurity(rn[:, -1],criterion))
            if ig > max_ig:
                max_ig = ig
                best_feature = i
                best_value = k
                best_ln = ln.copy()
                best_rn = rn.copy()
    if max_ig <= 0:
        return 0
    left_n = Node(best_feature, best_value, None, None, impurity(best_ln[:, -1],criterion), best_ln)
    right_n = Node(best_feature, best_value, None, None, impurity(best_rn[:, -1],criterion), best_rn)
    best_ig(left_n,criterion)
    node.left_child = left_n
    best_ig(right_n,criterion)
    node.right_child = right_n
def tree_builder(xtrain, ytrain, xtest, criterion):
    xtrain_copy = np.concatenate([xtrain, ytrain[:, np.newaxis]], axis = 1)
    origin_node = Node(None, None, None, None, impurity(xtrain_copy[:, -1], criterion), xtrain_copy)
    best_ig(origin_node, criterion)
    ypred = np.array([])
    for i in xtest:
        node = origin_node
        while node.left_child is not None:
            if i[node.left_child.feature] == node.left_child.value:
                node = node.left_child
            else:
                node = node.right_child
        if (node.data[:, -1]==1).sum() > (node.data[:, -1]==0).sum():
            ypred = np.append(ypred, 1)
        else:
            ypred = np.append(ypred, 0)
    return ypred, origin_node
def tree_drawer(node, level):
    i = level
    string = ""
    
    if node.left_child is None:
        return ""
    lnode = node.left_child
    string += tree_drawer(lnode, level-1)
    rnode = node.right_child
    string += tree_drawer(rnode, level-1)
    if level == 1:
        c1 = ""
        c2 = ""
        if node.left_child.left_child is None:
            if (node.data[:, -1]==1).sum() > (node.data[:, -1]==0).sum():
                c1 = "1"
            else:
                c1 = "0"
        if node.right_child.left_child is None:
            if (node.data[:, -1]==1).sum() > (node.data[:, -1]==0).sum():
                c2 = "1"
            else:
                c2 = "0"
        string = "feature " + str(node.left_child.feature) + " = " + str(node.left_child.value) + "? " + c1 + "     " + "feature " + str(node.right_child.feature) + " != " + str(node.right_child.value) + "? " + c2 + "             " 
        return string
    return string

x_valid_svm = scale(x_valid_svm)

Implementing The Solution

# Output prediction function
def svm_predict(features, weights):
    features = np.float_(features)
    weights = np.float_(weights)
    return np.matmul(weights, features.T)

# Hinge-Loss function
def hinge_loss(ytest, preds):
    ytest = np.float_(ytest)
    preds = np.float_(preds)
    return np.maximum(0, 1 - ytest * preds)

# Gradient function
def svm_update_weights(xtrain, ytrain, weights, learnrate, C): 
    C = (hinge_loss(ytrain, svm_predict(xtrain, weights))!=0) * C 
    weights  = weights - learnrate * (1/len(ytrain)) * np.sum(-(xtrain*ytrain[:,np.newaxis])* C[:, np.newaxis] + weights, axis = 0)
    return weights

# Classification function
def classify(preds):
    return (preds >= 0).astype(int)
np.random.seed(3)
def svm(xtrain, ytrain, xvalid, yvalid, xtest, ytest, C, epochs = 1000, learnrate = 0.01):
    xtrain = np.insert(xtrain, 0, values=1, axis=1)
    xvalid = np.insert(xvalid, 0, values=1, axis=1)
    ytrain = np.where(ytrain <= 0, -1, 1)
    weights = np.random.uniform(size = xtrain.shape[1])
    max_acc = 0
    opt_weights = weights
    print("TRAINING & VALIDATING... \n")
    for i in range(epochs):
        for k in range(10):
            weights = svm_update_weights(xtrain, ytrain, weights, learnrate, C)
        preds = svm_predict(xvalid, weights)
        validation_classified_preds = classify(svm_predict(xvalid, weights))
        acc = accuracy_score(yvalid, validation_classified_preds)
        if max_acc < acc:
            max_acc = acc
            opt_weights = weights
        print("Epoch ", i*10)
        print("Hinge Loss = ", np.mean(hinge_loss(yvalid, preds)))
        print("Accuracy = ", acc)
        print("\n\n")
    print("\n\n")
    print("TESTING...")
    xtest = np.insert(xtest, 0, values=1, axis=1)
    preds_t = svm_predict(xtest, opt_weights)
    print("Hinge Loss = ", np.mean(hinge_loss(ytest, preds_t)))
    test_classified_preds = classify(svm_predict(xtest, opt_weights))
    acc = accuracy_score( ytest, test_classified_preds)
    print("Accuracy = ", acc)
    plt.title('Plotting The Predictions Against the Data')
    yt = np.matmul(opt_weights, xtrain.T)
    plt.plot(xtrain, yt, 'r.')
    plt.plot(xtrain, ytrain, 'b.')
    return test_classified_preds
svm_predictions = svm(x_train_svm, y_train_svm, x_valid_svm,y_valid_svm, x_test_svm, y_test_svm, C= 1000, epochs=100)
